58 // Get the number of parameters expected by function.
59 uint16_t parameter_count() const { return parameter_count_; }
60
61 // Get the number of locals required for bytecode array.
62 int locals_count() const {
63 DCHECK_GE(local_register_count_, 0);
64 return local_register_count_;
65 }
66
67 // Returns the number of fixed (non-temporary) registers.
68 int fixed_register_count() const { return locals_count(); }
69
70 // Returns the number of fixed and temporary registers.
71 int total_register_count() const {
72 DCHECK_LE(fixed_register_count(),
73 register_allocator()->maximum_register_count());
74 return register_allocator()->maximum_register_count();
75 }

287 // Call a JS function which is known to be a property of a JS object. The
288 // JSFunction or Callable to be called should be in |callable|. The arguments
289 // should be in |args|, with the receiver in |args[0]|. The call type of the
290 // expression is in |call_type|. Type feedback is recorded in the
291 // |feedback_slot| in the type feedback vector.
292 BytecodeArrayBuilder& CallProperty(Register callable, RegisterList args,
293 int feedback_slot);
294
295 // Call a JS function with an known undefined receiver. The JSFunction or
296 // Callable to be called should be in |callable|. The arguments should be in
297 // |args|, with no receiver as it is implicitly set to undefined. Type
298 // feedback is recorded in the |feedback_slot| in the type feedback vector.
299 BytecodeArrayBuilder& CallUndefinedReceiver(Register callable,
300 RegisterList args,
301 int feedback_slot);
302
303 // Call a JS function with an any receiver, possibly (but not necessarily)
304 // undefined. The JSFunction or Callable to be called should be in |callable|.
305 // The arguments should be in |args|, with the receiver in |args[0]|. Type
306 // feedback is recorded in the |feedback_slot| in the type feedback vector.
307 BytecodeArrayBuilder& CallAnyReceiver(Register callable, RegisterList args,
308 int feedback_slot);
309
310 // Tail call into a JS function. The JSFunction or Callable to be called
311 // should be in |callable|. The arguments should be in |args|, with the
312 // receiver in |args[0]|. Type feedback is recorded in the |feedback_slot| in
313 // the type feedback vector.
314 BytecodeArrayBuilder& TailCall(Register callable, RegisterList args,
315 int feedback_slot);
316
317 // Call a JS function. The JSFunction or Callable to be called should be in
318 // |callable|, the receiver in |args[0]| and the arguments in |args[1]|
319 // onwards. The final argument must be a spread.
320 BytecodeArrayBuilder& CallWithSpread(Register callable, RegisterList args,
321 int feedback_slot);
322
323 // Call the Construct operator. The accumulator holds the |new_target|.
324 // The |constructor| is in a register and arguments are in |args|.
325 BytecodeArrayBuilder& Construct(Register constructor, RegisterList args,
326 int feedback_slot);
327
328 // Call the Construct operator for use with a spread. The accumulator holds
329 // the |new_target|. The |constructor| is in a register and arguments are in
330 // |args|. The final argument must be a spread.
331 BytecodeArrayBuilder& ConstructWithSpread(Register constructor,
332 RegisterList args,
333 int feedback_slot);
334
335 // Call the Construct operator, forwarding all arguments passed to the current
336 // interpreted frame, including the receiver. The accumulator holds the
337 // |new_target|. The |constructor| is in a register.
338 BytecodeArrayBuilder& ConstructForwardAllArgs(Register constructor,
339 int feedback_slot);

527 base::Optional<BytecodeSourceInfo> MaybePopSourcePosition(int scope_start) {
528 if (!latest_source_info_.is_valid() ||
529 latest_source_info_.source_position() < scope_start) {
530 return base::nullopt;
531 }
532 BytecodeSourceInfo source_info = latest_source_info_;
533 latest_source_info_.set_invalid();
534 return source_info;
535 }
536
537 void PushSourcePosition(BytecodeSourceInfo source_info) {
538 DCHECK(!latest_source_info_.is_valid());
539 latest_source_info_ = source_info;
540 }
541
542 void SetStatementPosition(int position) {
543 if (position == kNoSourcePosition) return;
544 latest_source_info_.MakeStatementPosition(position);
545 }
546
547 void SetExpressionPosition(Expression* expr) {
548 SetExpressionPosition(expr->position());
549 }
550
551 void SetExpressionPosition(int position) {
552 if (position == kNoSourcePosition) return;
553 if (!latest_source_info_.is_statement()) {
554 // Ensure the current expression position is overwritten with the
555 // latest value.
556 latest_source_info_.MakeExpressionPosition(position);
557 }
558 }
559
560 void SetExpressionAsStatementPosition(Expression* expr) {
561 SetStatementPosition(expr->position());
562 }
